Now we will compute the average dependency distance:

- Total distances = 1 + 1 + 2 + 1 + 1 + 1 + 1 + 1 + 6 + 1 + 1 + 2 + 1 + 1 + 1 + 1 + 1 + 1 = 30
- Total tokens = 19 (including all tokens)

Average dependency distance = Total distances / Number of dependencies.

Note that there were 12 dependencies between heads and dependents. Thus, we need to consider only those dependencies associated with head-dependent relationships.

Calculating the average:

